abstract: The company is joining other oil companies and corporate giants to endorse a plan from the Climate Leadership Council to tax fossil fuels and pay the dividends to taxpayers.
snippet: The company is joining other oil companies and corporate giants to endorse a plan from the Climate Leadership Council to tax fossil fuels and pay the dividends to taxpayers.
lead_paragraph: Exxon Mobil, other oil companies and a number of other corporate giants announced on Tuesday that they are supporting a plan to tax carbon emissions that was put forth this year by a group of Republican elder statesmen.

abstract: Without an extension from the State Legislature, the power that the mayor has to choose the city school chancellor and set educational policy will expire at the end of June.
snippet: Without an extension from the State Legislature, the power that the mayor has to choose the city school chancellor and set educational policy will expire at the end of June.
lead_paragraph: There’s still not much love in Albany for Mayor Bill de Blasio. Hoping to win a last-minute deal in the Legislature to extend mayoral control over city schools, he telephoned the leader of the Republicans in the State Senate, John J. Flanagan, on Monday morning.

headline_main: The Decline of the Baronial C.E.O.

abstract: John Mackey wanted to fight off the activist investors attacking Whole Foods. He found a savior in Amazon, a company blamed for laying waste to retailers.
snippet: John Mackey wanted to fight off the activist investors attacking Whole Foods. He found a savior in Amazon, a company blamed for laying waste to retailers.
lead_paragraph: Since John Mackey co-founded a precursor to Whole Foods in 1978, he has taken a hands-on management approach to the organic grocery chain. He personally oversaw each step of its national expansion. During a takeover battle 10 years ago, Mr. Mackey used a pseudonym to write anonymous blog posts attacking a competitor.

abstract: Nearly every city agency has more workers now than when Mayor Bill de Blasio took office, and there’s been a surge in civilian hiring in law enforcement.
snippet: Nearly every city agency has more workers now than when Mayor Bill de Blasio took office, and there’s been a surge in civilian hiring in law enforcement.
lead_paragraph: After serving a tour in the sticky rice and fruit fields of northeast Thailand for the Peace Corps, Leanne Spaulding landed a job at a Virginia-based trade association, working her way to a master’s degree from Duke University in environmental management.

abstract: The lack of an African-American challenger in the mayoral race highlights the absence of a rising generation of black politicians in New York.
snippet: The lack of an African-American challenger in the mayoral race highlights the absence of a rising generation of black politicians in New York.
lead_paragraph: Among New Yorkers in the brownstone-occupying territories, which is to say in many of the places that elected him in the first place, it is common to encounter a sense of bewildered frustration at the notion that Mayor Bill de Blasio faces almost no opposition in his race for a second term. How is this possible when rates of homelessness have risen, when towers are going up in communities that don’t want them, when so many seem to have so little enthusiasm for him on a personal level?

abstract: The office messaging company is not yet profitable, but new funding could raise its valuation to $5 billion as it faces rivals like Microsoft’s Teams.
snippet: The office messaging company is not yet profitable, but new funding could raise its valuation to $5 billion as it faces rivals like Microsoft’s Teams.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Slack, an office messaging company, is in talks to raise around $500 million at a valuation around $5 billion, according to two people with knowledge of the discussions, who were not authorized to speak publicly about the financing.
